{
  "text": "In this study, EUS-guided TM was technically successful in over 96.8% of the patients with pseudocysts. This high technical success rate is comparable and in agreement to those previously reported [8-10, 14, 16-23] . On the contrary, the technical success of TP in patients who underwent CD was significantly lower (46%). Placement of a bridging stent across the PD disruption for TP has been correlated with improved treatment outcomes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In this study,",
